ENTRY            A0724   20260205   20260401   20260401       A131
SUBENT        A0724001   20260205   20260401   20260401       A131
BIB                 10         28
TITLE      Neutron removal and cluster breakup of 14B and 14Be
AUTHOR     (N.I.Ashwood,M.Freer,J.C.Angelique,V.Bouchat,
           W.N.Catford,N.M.Clarke,N.Curtis,O.Dorvaux,F.Hanappe,
           Y.Kerckx,M.Labiche,J.L.Lecouey,F.M.Marques,T.Materna,
           A.Ninane,G.Normand,N.A.Orr,S.Pain,N.Soic,L.Stuttge,
           C.Timis,A.Unshakova,V.A.Ziman)
REFERENCE  (J,PR/C,70,024608,2004)
INSTITUTE  (2UK BIR,2FR CAE,2BLGBRU,2UK SUR,2FR ULP,2BLGLVN,
           4ZZZDUB,2UK UWS)
FACILITY   (ACCEL,2FR GAN)
INC-SOURCE The 14Be and 14B secondary beams were produced via
           fragmentation of a 63 MeV/A 18O primary beam on a
           rotating 9Be target. Particle identification was
           achieved via time-of-flight through the LISE
           spectrometer.
SAMPLE     The beam was tracked onto a 275 mg/cm2 carbon target
           using two drift chambers.
DETECTOR   (MAGSP) LISE3 magnetic spectrometer.
           (TELES,SISD,CSICR) Si-CsI telescopes.
            SISD- The Si elements were placed 16 cm from the
           target and consisted of two 500 um thick 2.5*2.5 cm2
           position-sensitive strip detectors.
           (SCIN) Neutrons were detected using the Demon array
           of 91 liquid scintillator modules.
           ~100 liquid scintillators were used.
METHOD     (EDE,TOF,COINC)
HISTORY    (20091222C) SD
           (20260205U) SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              28
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           31
